The paper deals with the development of a new algorithm for computed tomography image formation using energy selective, photon counting X-ray detectors. This involves the use of a multilinear image model and tensor-based regularizers. The paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image formation and reconstruction. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category as it involves the use of iterative algorithms and regularization techniques. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as tensor-based modeling and regularization, which may make it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper may also belong to the Mathematical Modeling (cs.MM) category as it involves the use of mathematical models for image reconstruction. Finally, the paper may belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) category as it involves the use of numerical methods for solving the optimization problem.
